adroit
	adj. clever or skillful in using the hands or mind
eclectic
	adj. deriving ideas, style, or taste from a broad and diverse range of sources
prolix
	adj. (of speech or writing) using or containing too many words; tediously lengthy
obduracy
	n. resoluteness by virtue of being unyielding and inflexible
mercurial
	adj. (of a person) subject to sudden unpredictable changes of mood or mind
pastoral
	adj. (especially of land or a farm) used for or related to the keeping or grazing of sheep or cattle
perspicacity
	n. the quality of having a ready insight of things; shrewdness
callousness
	n. insensitive and cruel disregard for others
cursory
	adj. hasty and therefore not thorough or detailed
inquest
	n. legal or judicial inquiry, especially before a jury and especially made by a coroner into the cause of someone's death
